5.14.20  5:56 pm   There is a beautiful moment in 'when i get older', at the lyrics '...then the song will sing me...'. I really love it but I am not sure what that is called. I want to say key change, is that right? My music knowledge is mostly centered around appreciating it, but would be nice to know what things are in case I need to explain it to someone else.

      well, ..... sort of, yes, but, if we say that then we have to also admit that the exact same thing happened earlier, with 'here's a poem about rain.' The melody/chords etc is the same in both places. if i recall correctly, the main difference the second time around is the drums slam much harder, which has nothing to do with key
